headline.main: U.S. Prosecutors Fight Ruling Limiting Foreign Bribery Cases
headline.print_headline: U.S. Prosecutors Fight Ruling Limiting Foreign Bribery Cases

lead_paragraph: For the second time, a New Jersey prosecutor has declined to pursue a resident's criminal misconduct case against Republican Gov. Chris Christie over the George Washington Bridge lane closure scandal.
